                <item>
                 <widget class="QTextEdit" name="notesBox">
                  <property name="readOnly">
                   <bool>true</bool>
                  </property>
                  <property name="html">
                   <string>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC &quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd&quot;&gt;
&lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=&quot;qrichtext&quot; content=&quot;1&quot; /&gt;&lt;meta charset=&quot;utf-8&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=&quot;text/css&quot;&gt;
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=&quot; font-family:'Sans Serif'; font-size:10pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Thread tool: use a metric tap for internal threads and a die profile for external threads.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Method: cut thread geometry rather than cosmetic representations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Chamfer: add a 45° lead-in, ideally at least 1.0 mm long.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Walls: target 4–6 perimeters for strength and clean thread form.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Orientation: print vertically when possible to maintain circularity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:8px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• The calculator values are optimized as practical starting points for test fits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;&quot;&gt;• Originally tuned around SolidWorks-style modeling, but portable to other CAD packages.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;</string>
                  </property>
                 </widget>
                </item>
               </layout>
              </widget>
